# ESLint flat config side-effect safety

When authoring shared ESLint flat configs in `packages/config`, do not import legacy config modules that execute side effects on import (for example, modules that call `@rushstack/eslint-patch`).

Instead:

- Convert required rules into first-party flat config modules in `src/eslint/`.
- Depend directly on the plugins/parsers those rules need.
- Keep runtime imports explicit in `tsup.config.ts` externals.

## Why

Side-effectful legacy config imports can break standalone consumers (outside the monorepo) because patch modules often assume ESLint invocation context.
